Key Match Events: Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Houston Rockets 126-107.
Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Chet Holmgren combined for a total of 58 points.
Oklahoma City Thunder shot 51% from the field and nearly 38% from 3-point range.
Six players from Oklahoma City Thunder finished with double-digit points.
Jalen Williams and Isaiah Joe each added 14 points.
Ajay Mitchell scored 12 points and had seven assists off the bench.
Post-Match Reflections: The win showed that the Thunder might be finding its stride offensively.
Oklahoma City remains at the top of the NBA defensive rating ladder with a 97.3 rating.
Holmgren's shot-blocking prowess and Williams' high league-leading steal numbers have been significant for the Thunder's defense.
The Thunder tied its season-low of 16 forced turnovers.
